Mr. Coolidge.

174
00:11:20,913 --> 00:11:23,609
- Oh. Just one more thing.
- Hmm?

175
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:26,846
What's a bobsled?

176
00:11:28,387 --> 00:11:30,651
That's a bobsled!

177
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:34,591
Oh! So a bobsled is
a pushcart with no wheels.

178
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:38,255
- That's what it looks like here.
- Let me see that.

179
00:11:42,101 --> 00:11:45,434
All right. "The key elements
for a successful sled team...

180
00:11:45,504 --> 00:11:49,998
are a steady driver and three strong
runners to push off down the ice."

181
00:11:50,076 --> 00:11:53,341
Ice! Ice!

182
00:11:53,412 --> 00:11:58,873
Well... it's kind of
a winter sport, you know.

183
00:11:58,951 --> 00:12:03,115
- You mean winter as in ice?
- Maybe.

184
00:12:03,189 --> 00:12:07,182
You mean winter as in igloos
and Eskimos and penguins and ice?

185
00:12:07,259 --> 00:12:10,660
- Possibly.
- See ya.

186
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:13,528
- Where you goin'?
- I'm gonna take a hot bath.

187
00:12:13,599 --> 00:12:15,726
I'm gettin' cold just thinkin'
about all this ice.

188
00:12:15,801 --> 00:12:18,361
No, man! You're gonna be
part of my bobsled team.

189
00:12:18,437 --> 00:12:20,371
What you need me for?

190
00:12:20,439 --> 00:12:23,272
Who... is the best
pushcart driver...

191
00:12:23,342 --> 00:12:26,106
- In all of Jamaica?
- You're lookin' at him!

192
00:12:26,178 --> 00:12:29,113
- Then you're gonna do it?
- No!

193
00:12:29,181 --> 00:12:31,342
Hey, man, you could be famous.

194
00:12:31,417 --> 00:12:35,012
You could have your picture
on a Wheaties box.

195
