favorite showed his true colors
with that late stretch run.

228
00:14:11,584 --> 00:14:14,417
- Uh-huh.
- Tumbleweed held on momentarily,
but realistically,

229
00:14:14,486 --> 00:14:17,148
only a fool would put
their money on Tumbleweed.

230
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:21,023
- That horse had no chance whatsoev...
- Uh-huh! Uh-huh! Uh-huh!

231
00:14:21,093 --> 00:14:23,823
Uh-huh! Uh-huh!

232
00:14:23,896 --> 00:14:26,490
That guy won two gold medals?

233
00:14:29,001 --> 00:14:32,596
I think so.

234
00:14:32,671 --> 00:14:36,607
[Sighs]

235
00:14:36,675 --> 00:14:40,702
That's Tumbleweed gone.
Okay, next race.

236
00:14:44,149 --> 00:14:47,482
Excuse, me.
Are you Mr. Irving Blitzer?

237
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,714
Well, that depends
on who's asking.

238
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:53,588
My name is Derice Bannock.
This is my teammate, Sanka Coffie.

239
00:14:53,659 --> 00:14:55,820
Greetings, sled god.

240
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:58,022
We were just wondering
if you'd be interested...

241
00:14:58,097 --> 00:15:02,227
in coaching the first
Jamaican bobsled team.

242
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:05,566
Derice, remember the radio?
Radio?

243
00:15:05,638 --> 00:15:08,664
Stick. Shooting
with the stick. Let's go!

244
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:11,107
Let's go, Derice!

245
00:15:23,889 --> 00:15:26,221
Come on, coach.

246
00:15:26,292 --> 00:15:29,557
Just help me get started.

247
00:15:29,628 --> 00:15:31,596
[Derice Groans]

248
00:15:40,239 --> 00:15:42,230
- Oh!
- Greetings, sled god.

249
00:15:42,308 --> 00:15:46,404
- Sorry to bother you, but you're
the only one who can help us.
- Get out! Get out!

250
00:15:46,478 --> 00:15:50,414
[Sighs, Groans]

251
00:15:50,482 --> 00:15:52,416
[Toilet Flushing]

252
00:15:54,753 --> 00:15:58,018
- Go away.
- Okay.

253
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:00,354
Nice to meet you!

254
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:03,759
- Maybe today is a bad day.
- Yeah.

255
00:16:03,829 --> 00:16:08,732
I'll come back tomorrow.
And the next day. And the next day.

256
00:16:08,801 --> 00:16:12,237
- No! Look, whatever your name is...
- Derice.

257
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:15,796
All right, Derice. Let me lay out
some difficulties for you.

258
00:16:15,874 --> 00:16:20,470
Snow. You don't have any.
It's 900 degrees out there.

259
00:16:20,546 --> 00:16:24,346
Time. You don't have any.
The Olympics are in three months.

260
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:27,977
And me. You don't have me.

261
00:16:28,053 --> 00:16:31,454
As far as I'm concerned, the sport
of bobsledding no longer exists.

262
00:16:31,523 --> 00:16:34,048
I don't want to do it,
I don't want to coach it,

263
00:16:34,126 --> 00:16:37,391
and most of all,
and I mean most of all,

264
00:16:37,463 --> 00:16:41,729
I don't want to be within
2,000 miles of anyone who does.

265
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,734
Now, did you follow all that?

266
00:16:43,802 --> 00:16:46,362
Then how come you still have
that poster on the wall?

267
00:16:48,974 --> 00:16:52,307
Is that what's bothering you?

268
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:59,417
There. Is that better?
Are you happy?

269
00:17:06,725 --> 00:17:10,752
Like I said...
my name is Derice Bannock.

270
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:13,821
I'm Ben Bannock's son.

271
00:17:17,469 --> 00:17:20,927
I haven't seen this picture
in 20 years.

272
00:17:21,006 --> 00:17:25,033
Huh. Would you look at me then?

273
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:28,045
Whoo. Would you look at me now.

274
00:17:28,113 --> 00:17:32,015
Please, Mr. Blitzer,
just give me a chance.

275
00:17:32,084 --> 00:17:35,349
If I don't have what it takes,
we'll forget the whole thing.

276
00:17:35,421 --> 00:17:37,946
Believe me, kid,
you do not have what it takes.

277
00:17:38,023 --> 00:17:40,821
- But you thought my father did.
- Your father was one of...

278
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:44,226
the toughest competitors I ever saw.

279
00:17:44,296 --> 00:17:47,561
He ran the 100 meters in ten-flat.

280
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:50,693
Well, I run it in nine-nine.

281
00:17:52,771 --> 00:17:56,832
Come on. Coach me.

282
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:02,176
Sorry.
You're a couple decades late.

283
00:18:02,247 --> 00:18:05,375
Oh, I see. It might be easy
for you to walk away from me,

284
00:18:05,451 --> 00:18:08,352
Mr. Blitzer, but you can't
walk away from this:

285
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,547
Twenty years ago
you came down here to see...

286
00:18:10,622 --> 00:18:13,716
if you could make a Jamaican sprinter
into a bobsledder,

287
00:18:13,792 --> 00:18:16,192
and you never got that chance.

288
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:20,357
Look at me, Mr. Blitzer.
I'm your chance.

289
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:22,525
Take it.

290
00:18:27,005 --> 00:18:28,939
[Exhaling]

291
00:18:29,108 --> 00:18:32,168
- [Crowd Chattering]
- " [Reggae]

292
00:18:33,645 --> 00:18:36,045
All right.
Everyone quiet down.

293
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:40,017
Nice group here.
Now, for two of you lucky people,

294
00:18:40,085 --> 00:18:43,782
our trip to the Olympics
starts right now.

295
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:49,490
And I want to introduce you...
to Mr. Irving Blitzer...

296
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:53,019
who's going to be
our expert bobsled coach.

297
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:57,068
Sanka. Hit it, man.

298
00:18:57,136 --> 00:19:01,630
You're on the air, sled god.

299
00:19:01,707 --> 00:19:04,972
Gentlemen, a bobsled
is a simple thing.

300
00:19:05,043 --> 00:19:06,977
[Man]
Yeah, so's a toilet!

301
00:19:07,045 --> 00:19:09,605
[Crowd Laughing]

302
00:19:09,681 --> 00:19:13,674
Thank you. Thank you very much.
Basically, what you're looking to do...

303
00:19:13,752 --> 00:19:19,122
is get your sorry rear ends from the top
of an icy chute to the bottom.

304
00:19:19,191 --> 00:19:22,683
You're ziggin', you're zaggin'.

305
00:19:22,761 --> 00:19:26,788
It's the biggest, coldest
roller coaster you've ever been on.

306
00:19:28,534 --> 00:19:30,559
Ice.

307
00:19:32,337 --> 00:19:34,999
Oooh. Ooh.
[Chuckles]

308
00:19:35,073 --> 00:19:39,442
[Irv]
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

309
00:19:39,511 --> 00:19:42,412
I almost forgot, uh...

310
00:19:42,481 --> 00:19:45,644
One minor drawback
to this delightful winter sport...

311
00:19:45,717 --> 00:19:48,311
is the high-speed crash.

312
00:19:48,387 --> 00:19:50,651
That hurt. Ah.

313
00:19:50,722 --> 00:19:55,182
Always remember, your bones
will not break in a bobsled.

314
00:19:55,260 --> 00:19:57,285
No, no. They shatter.

315
00:19:59,898 --> 00:20:02,366
Eee!

316
00:20:04,403 --> 00:20:08,237
So... who wants in?

317
00:20:22,688 --> 00:20:25,953
Look. Baldy's here.

318
00:20:26,024 --> 00:20:28,049
Glad you could make it, man.

319
00:20:28,126 --> 00:20:32,995
- Don't touch me!
- No problem.

320
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:36,228
- So what's your name?
- Yul Brenner.

321
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:42,896
Well, it's good to have you
as a teammate, Brenner.

322
00:20:42,975 --> 00:20:45,808
Let's get one thing straight,
Bannock.

323
00:20:45,877 --> 00:20:50,541
We may be on the same team,
but I am no one's teammate.

324
00:20:50,616 --> 00:20:53,210
- Long as you come here to bobsled...
- Hey, listen, man,

325
00:20:53,285 --> 00:20:55,515
the only reason why I come here...

326
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:59,182
is to get off
of this stinkin' island.

327
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:04,321
If I have to take one of those bobsleds
to do it, then all right.

328
00:21:04,396 --> 00:21:07,331
- No problem.
- [Irv] Ah, yes.

329
00:21:07,399 --> 00:21:11,096
Yes, I have a problem. There's
no such thing as a three-man sled.

330
00:21:11,169 --> 00:21:14,263
You're one Jamaican short.

331
00:21:14,339 --> 00:21:17,433
Hey.

332
00:21:17,509 --> 00:21:20,740
The meeting start yet?
Uh-oh.

333
00:21:20,812 --> 00:21:24,111
You! I'll kill you.

334
00:21:24,182 --> 00:21:26,309
- [Derice] Wait! Hold on!
- College boy, I'll kill you!

335
00:21:26,385 --> 00:21:29,013
[Sanka] Hey, think, man, think!
Easy! Whoa! Down, boy!

336
00:21:29,087 --> 00:21:31,920
[Men Shouting, Chair Clattering]

337
00:21:31,990 --> 00:21:35,426
Kill him
and we don't have a team.

338
00:21:35,494 --> 00:21:37,860
I'm not ridin'
in the same sled as that.

339
00:21:37,929 --> 00:21:40,898
He tripped me too, you know.
But in case you haven't noticed,

340
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:43,366
there's no one else here.

341
00:21:43,435 --> 00:21:46,336
- You're crowdin' me, slinky head.
- [Chuckling]

342
00:21:46,405 --> 00:21:48,339
Slinky head.
That's a good one.

343
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:50,875
- What are you laughing about?
- Nothing.

344
00:21:50,942 --> 00:21:55,345
If it wasn't for you, rich boy,
I'd be in the Olympics right now.

345
00:21:55,414 --> 00:21:58,008
I don't know what you all are arguing
about 'cause Derice was gonna...

346
00:21:58,083 --> 00:22:01,519
- Beat both of your butts anyway.
- What are you talkin' about?

347
00:22:01,586 --> 00:22:04,555
- How 'bout I beat your butt right now?
- How 'bout I draw a line...

348
00:22:04,623 --> 00:22:06,989
down the middle of your head
so it looks like a butt?

349
00:22:07,059 --> 00:22:08,993
[Chuckling]

350
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:15,696
Forget it, man, I'm gone.

351
00:22:15,767 --> 00:22:18,463
[Derice]
Fine. Stay here on the island.

352
00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:21,700
We're going to Canada.

353
00:22:25,210 --> 00:22:29,476
All right. I'll do it.

354
00:22:29,548 --> 00:22:33,348
But you better tell
this mama's boy...

355
00:22:33,418 --> 00:22:35,784
to stay the hell away from me.

356
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:38,254
You understand?

357
00:22:38,323 --> 00:22:41,690
No problem.

358
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:45,992
Hey, Irv.
Say hello to the first...

359
00:22:46,064 --> 00:22:48,760
Jamaican bobsled team.

360
00:22:55,507 --> 00:22:58,203
Oh, goody.

361
00:22:58,276 --> 00:23:02,645
Gentlemen,
this... is a bobsled.

362
00:23:02,714 --> 00:23:05,342
Sort of.

363
00:23:05,417 --> 00:23:08,818
- All right, here's what
we're gonna do. Yul...
- Don't touch me.

364
00:23:08,887 --> 00:23:12,823
Of course. Sorry. You're
gonna be the second middleman.

365
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:16,987
You're strong, you're fast
and you're gonna love that seat.

366
00:23:17,062 --> 00:23:19,121
Junior,
you're the first middleman.

367
00:23:19,197 --> 00:23:22,963
You're quick, you're sharp.
Hop in. Sanka.

368
00:23:23,034 --> 00:23:26,003
- I know. I'm the driver, right?
- No, you're the brakeman.

369
00:23:26,071 --> 00:23:30,440
- No, no, I'm the driver.
- No, you're not. You're the brakeman.

370
00:23:30,509 --> 00:23:33,842
- I'm the driver.
- You're not. You're the brakeman.

371
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:35,880
You don't understand.
I am Sanka Coffie.

372
00:23:35,947 --> 00:23:38,541
I'm the best pushcart driver
in all of Jamaica.

373
00:23:38,617 --> 00:23:42,178
I must drive.
Do you dig where I'm coming from?

374
00:23:42,254 --> 00:23:44,188
- Yeah, I dig where you're coming from.
- Good.

375
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:47,350
Now dig where I'm coming from.
I'm coming from two gold medals.

376
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:50,918
I'm coming from nine world records
in both the two and four-man events.

377
00:23:50,996 --> 00:23:53,692
I'm coming from ten years
of intense competition...

378
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:56,165
with the best athletes
in the world.

379
00:23:56,234 --> 00:23:58,464
That's a hell of a place
to be comin' from.

380
00:23:58,537 --> 00:24:02,098
You see, Sanka, the driver
has to work harder than anyone.

381
00:24:02,174 --> 00:24:04,734
He's the first to show up
and the last to leave.

382
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:07,040
When his teammates
are all out drinkin' beer,

383
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:09,910
he's up in his room
studying pictures of turns.

384
00:24:09,981 --> 00:24:14,611
You see, a driver must remain
focused 100% at all times.

385
00:24:14,686 --> 00:24:18,747
Not only is he responsible for knowing
every inch of every course he races,

386
00:24:18,824 --> 00:24:22,351
he's also responsible for the lives
of the other three people in his sled.

387
00:24:23,995 --> 00:24:26,463
Now, do you want
that responsibility?

388
00:24:26,531 --> 00:24:28,624
I say we make Derice
the driver.

389
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:32,136
So do l, Sanka. So do I.

390
00:24:32,204 --> 00:24:35,731
[Sighs]

391
00:24:36,908 --> 00:24:39,399
Oh. The back is nice.

392
00:24:39,478 --> 00:24:43,073
[Junior]
All right, Father, listen here.

393
00:24:43,148 --> 00:24:47,983
Ya see, I've made up my mind.
I am going to be a bobsledder.

394
00:24:48,053 --> 00:24:51,250
That's right. A bobsledder.

395
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:54,486
- [Dog Barks, Whines]
- Oh, really?

396
00:24:54,559 --> 00:24:57,790
Well, I'm sorry
you feel that way.

397
00:24:57,863 --> 00:25:03,301
Fine. Cut off my allowance,
because you see, Father,

398
00:25:03,368 --> 00:25:07,771
a man has got to do
what a man has got to do.

399
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:13,603
[Car Horn Honking]

400
00:25:18,183 --> 00:25:22,176
- Just who I want to see.
- M-M-Me?

401
00:25:22,254 --> 00:25:26,122
- You know where I just came from?
- W-Where?

402
00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:31,356
I got you a job.
With Webster, Webster and Cohen,

403
00:25:31,429 --> 00:25:33,795
the biggest brokerage house in Miami.

404
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:36,459
Oh, right.
Webster, Webster and Cohen.

405
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:40,528
[Chuckling] That's right.
And you start end of the month.

406
00:25:43,275 --> 00:25:45,971
- Yes, but I thought that I would...
- Look.

407
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:50,003
We went along with
this track nonsense long enough.

408
00:25:50,081 --> 00:25:54,211
And we agreed that it's time
to get on with your real future.

409
00:25:54,286 --> 00:25:56,584
Right?

410
00:25:56,655 --> 00:25:59,556
- I know...
- Right?

411
00:25:59,624 --> 00:26:02,320
- Yes, sir.
- Good.

412
00:26:02,394 --> 00:26:05,420
[Chuckles]

413
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:09,228
I'm gonna tell your mother.
[Chuckling]

414
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:23,638
- I guess we sure told him.
- [Whining]

415
00:26:23,782 --> 00:26:27,912
Winning a bobsled race is about
one thing: the push start.

416
00:26:27,986 --> 00:26:32,685
Now I know you dainty little
track stars think you're fast.

417
00:26:32,757 --> 00:26:37,990
Well, heh, let's see how fast you are
when you push a 600-pound sled.

418
00:26:38,063 --> 00:26:42,500
Now a respectable start time
is 5.7 seconds.

419
00:26:42,567 --> 00:26:45,593
If you speed demons can't
whip off an even six-flat,

420
00:26:45,670 --> 00:26:48,468
then you have a better chance of
becoming a barbershop quartet.

421
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:50,633
[Groaning]

422
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:52,904
Derice, come on! Hey!

423
00:26:52,978 --> 00:26:57,881
- Junior, get in. Never mind.
- Ow!

424
00:26:57,949 --> 00:27:00,110
- [Laughing]
- Come on, fellas,
move it back. Let's go!

425
00:27:00,185 --> 00:27:04,952
' Here on this mountain top
oh-oh '

426
00:27:05,023 --> 00:27:07,617
- 14.3. No good.
- ' I've got some wild, wild life '

427
00:27:07,692 --> 00:27:10,855
- 13.5. 11.7.
- ' I've got some bills to pay, oh-oh '

428
00:27:10,929 --> 00:27:13,659
This is what it's all about.
This is where you win or lose the race.

429
00:27:13,732 --> 00:27:16,360
Right here in the push start.
This is where you're gonna practice,

430
00:27:16,434 --> 00:27:18,902
right here, right here in a Volkswagen,
you're gonna practice.

431
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:21,564
- [Yelling]
- No! Junior, quit falling down.

432
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:25,098
Come on, hustle!
Catch up to them. There you go.

433
00:27:25,176 --> 00:27:28,111
Whoa. No! Do it again.

434
00:27:28,179 --> 00:27:32,548
[Sanka] Whoa, whoa. Stop, Derice!
Stop! Wait for me! Wait!

435
00:27:32,617 --> 00:27:35,450
I'm in! Stop!
Slow down!

436
00:27:35,520 --> 00:27:37,613
[Yelling, Crashing]

437
00:27:37,689 --> 00:27:40,749
Great. Very good.
Try it again.

438
00:27:42,460 --> 00:27:46,021
If I've said it once,
I've said it 46 times:

439
00:27:46,097 --> 00:27:49,658
Cold weather endurance is vital
to building a successful sled team.

440
00:27:53,071 --> 00:27:55,539
Cold enough?
[Chuckling]

441
00:27:57,442 --> 00:28:02,038
One, two, three!

442
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:05,480
[All]
Aaaah!

443
00:28:07,886 --> 00:28:10,650
- ' Wild, wild life '
- [Sanka] Go! Go! Go!

444
00:28:16,995 --> 00:28:19,862
- ' Here on this mountain top '
- [Sanka] Whoa! Slow down!

445
00:28:19,931 --> 00:28:22,422
- ' Oh-oh "
- [Derice] Sanka, hit the brakes, man!

446
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:25,025
- I can't! It's stuck!
- [Derice] Hold on!

447
00:28:25,103 --> 00:28:26,968
Look out!

448
00:28:27,038 --> 00:28:31,475
[Yelling]

449
00:28:36,448 --> 00:28:39,542
[Groaning]

450
00:28:39,617 --> 00:28:43,018
- [Indistinct Police Radio]
- [People Chattering]

451
00:28:43,088 --> 00:28:46,489
- Sanka, you dead?
- [Groaning]

452
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:50,187
Yeah, man.

453
00:28:50,261 --> 00:28:54,493
[Man] What have you done to the
police unit? I should arrest you.

454
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:57,967
- [Man #2] Who owns this thing?
- We do, sir.

455
00:28:58,036 --> 00:29:01,904
- And who are you?
- The Jamaican bobsled team, sir.

456
00:29:03,441 --> 00:29:06,535
- [Laughing]
- [Laughing]

457
00:29:06,611 --> 00:29:09,205
Don't give me that business.
I wasn't born yesterday.

458
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:13,239
5.9! 5.9! You did it!
You did it! 5.9!

459
00:29:13,318 --> 00:29:17,277
We did it! We did it! 5.9!
Get outta the way! Get outta the way!

460
00:29:17,355 --> 00:29:19,380
5.9, guys! What?

461
00:29:19,457 --> 00:29:22,426
- Who are you?
- I'm their coach. You guys okay?

462
00:29:22,494 --> 00:29:25,292
- Yeah, man.
- [Irv] How's the sled?

463
00:29:25,363 --> 00:29:27,297
Sled's okay?
Well, it's in the wrong place.

464
00:29:27,365 --> 00:29:30,266
Get it back to the top of the hill!
Let's move it right now, you slackers!

465
00:29:30,335 --> 00:29:34,328
- Move it! Let's hustle!
Come on, you guys, move it!
- [Team Groaning]

466
00:29:34,405 --> 00:29:35,838
[Thunder Rumbling]

467
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:39,172
[Irv] I'm not asking
for a winter sports program.

468
00:29:39,244 --> 00:29:43,772
All I need is a lousy 20 grand so I
can get us to the Olympics. That's all.

469
00:29:43,848 --> 00:29:46,749
[Coolidge] How in God's name
are you going to get to the Olympics?

470
00:29:46,818 --> 00:29:49,343
These boys have never even
seen a sled race before.

471
00:29:49,420 --> 00:29:53,254
Mr. Coolidge, I have been looking
at sledders since I was 12 years old.

472
00:29:53,324 --> 00:29:57,351
If I say these kids
can make it to the Olympics,
they can make it to the Olympics.

473
00:29:57,428 --> 00:30:00,920
Okay. Well, I'll
tell you what we'll do.

474
00:30:00,999 --> 00:30:03,297
Practice down here
with the boys a bit more,

475
00:30:03,368 --> 00:30:06,098
and when you're a little further along,
I'll come along and see you...

476
00:30:06,171 --> 00:30:10,608
- No! No, no!
- Now just a minute, Mr. Blitzer!

477
00:30:10,675 --> 00:30:13,166
This country enjoys
a fine athletic tradition.

478
00:30:13,244 --> 00:30:15,576
And if you think I'm gonna give you
the little money we have...

479
00:30:15,647 --> 00:30:19,174
so that you can parade us around
in front of the world like a freak show,

480
00:30:19,250 --> 00:30:21,548
you've got another thing coming.

481
00:30:21,619 --> 00:30:24,417
It's bad enough how you
embarrassed your own country.

482
00:30:24,489 --> 00:30:26,980
I'm certainly not gonna
allow you to embarrass ours.

483
00:30:29,494 --> 00:30:32,793
No go, kid.

484
00:30:32,864 --> 00:30:35,196
That's okay, coach.
We'll get the money.

485
00:30:35,266 --> 00:30:37,928
Do the words "give up"
mean anything to you?

486
00:30:38,002 --> 00:30:40,232
Not a thing.

487
00:30:40,305 --> 00:30:43,240
[Sanka] ' Some people say you know
they can't believe '

488
00:30:43,308 --> 00:30:45,674
' Jamaica
we have a bobsled team '

489
00:30:45,743 --> 00:30:48,473
' 'Nuff people say you know
they can't believe '

490
00:30:48,546 --> 00:30:51,310
' Jamaica
we have a bobsled team "

491
00:30:51,382 --> 00:30:55,910
Hi. I'm here to offer you
an opportunity of a lifetime.

492
00:30:55,987 --> 00:30:59,252
We're lookin' for a sponsor
for the first Jamaican bobsled team.

493
00:30:59,324 --> 00:31:03,260
[Laughing]

494
00:31:13,204 --> 00:31:16,037
[Crowd Chattering]

495
00:31:31,189 --> 00:31:32,816
[Crowd Cheering]

496
00:31:41,399 --> 00:31:44,334
[Crowd Chattering]

497
00:32:20,638 --> 00:32:23,937
- Oh!
- [Smacks Lips]

498
00:32:26,811 --> 00:32:30,212
' We have the one Derice
and the one Junior "

499
00:32:30,281 --> 00:32:33,910
I'll pay you a dollar to shut up.

500
00:32:37,088 --> 00:32:40,751
[Joy]
You got $9.52 from Yul Brenner.

501
00:32:40,825 --> 00:32:44,727
Thank you.
We got $184 from Derice and me.

502
00:32:44,796 --> 00:32:49,597
Sanka, how did your singing
on the street go?

503
00:32:49,667 --> 00:32:53,865
How did it go?
It went like this.

504
00:32:53,938 --> 00:32:56,236
' 'Nuff people say you know
they can't believe '

505
00:32:56,307 --> 00:32:58,468
- Sanka, we know.
- ' Jamaica, we have a bobsled team '

506
00:32:58,543 --> 00:33:00,101
- Sanka.
- ' We have the one Derice..."

507
00:33:00,178 --> 00:33:03,079
[All]
How much?

508
00:33:03,147 --> 00:33:06,446
- I made $1.16.
- [Irv] Oh, that's great.

509
00:33:06,517 --> 00:33:09,111
- We're only short about 19,000 bucks.
- [Beads Rattling]

510
00:33:09,187 --> 00:33:11,678
- Sorry I'm late, everybody.
- [Irv] No, really. That is terrific.

511
00:33:11,756 --> 00:33:16,159
You can unpack your suitcase,
Junior. We're not goin'.

512
00:33:16,227 --> 00:33:18,161
Hmm, that's too bad.

513
00:33:22,033 --> 00:33:25,093
- [Sanka Whistles]
- [Derice] Whoa.
Where'd you get it, man?

514
00:33:25,169 --> 00:33:29,105
- I sold my car.
- [Inhales] Yes, man.

515
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:31,607
- I am goin'!
- No, we're not.

516
00:33:31,676 --> 00:33:35,237
Look here, Junior, I appreciate
what you're trying to do here.

517
00:33:35,313 --> 00:33:38,248
But we can't accept this money.
It just wouldn't be proper.

518
00:33:38,316 --> 00:33:41,308
Aw, Derice, if I hadn't
tripped you fellas,

519
00:33:41,386 --> 00:33:43,980
we'd already been goin'
to the Olympics.

520
00:33:44,055 --> 00:33:47,115
I want you to have it.

521
00:33:51,729 --> 00:33:54,095
You mean you want us
to have it, right?

522
00:33:54,165 --> 00:33:56,292
Right. Us.

523
00:33:58,002 --> 00:34:01,165
Thanks a lot, Junior.
Thanks a whole heap, man.

524
00:34:01,239 --> 00:34:05,175
[Yul] Remember.
This doesn't mean that I like you.

525
00:34:05,243 --> 00:34:08,303
- You understand?
- [Joy] Be sure to thank
your father for us...

526
00:34:08,379 --> 00:34:10,540
'cause Lord knows he didn't
have to let you sell that car.

527
00:34:10,615 --> 00:34:13,482
Well, uh, he doesn't know
I sold the car.

528
00:34:13,551 --> 00:34:15,485
Um...
[Clears Throat]

529
00:34:15,553 --> 00:34:18,147
He doesn't know I'm
on the team, actually.

530
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:20,452
He thinks I'm off to Miami...

531
00:34:20,525 --> 00:34:22,720
and I loaned the car
to a friend to work for...

532
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:26,787
Webster, Webster and Cohen,
some place like that.

533
00:34:26,864 --> 00:34:30,300
- [All Laughing]
- ' Some people say you know
them can't believe '

534
00:34:30,368 --> 00:34:32,734
' Jamaica
we have a bobsled team '

535
00:34:32,804 --> 00:34:36,171
- ' We have the one Derice '
- ' And the one Junior '

536
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:38,231
' Yu... Sanka '

537
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:41,176
[Derice] ' The fastest of the fastest
of Jamaican sprinters '

538
00:34:41,245 --> 00:34:43,372
' Go to Olympics
Fight for Jamaica "

539
00:35:17,915 --> 00:35:23,376
[Man On P.A. Speaking French]

540
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:26,890
[Man On P.A.]
Welcome to Calgary, Alberta, Canada.

541
00:35:26,958 --> 00:35:29,518
- Come on.
- Home of the 1988 Winter Olympic Games.

542
00:35:29,594 --> 00:35:33,394
- This is it.
- We hope you all enjoy your stay.

543
00:36:07,665 --> 00:36:10,133
Sanka, man,
what you smokin'?

544
00:36:10,201 --> 00:36:14,228
[Coughing]
I'm not smokin'. I'm breathin'.

545
00:36:14,305 --> 00:36:16,239
[Coughing]

546
00:36:16,307 --> 00:36:19,071
All right, fellas,
this is us. Let's go.

547
00:36:19,143 --> 00:36:21,077
[Yelling]

548
00:36:21,145 --> 00:36:23,978
What's the matter?
You guys cold?

549
00:36:24,048 --> 00:36:27,609
It's not so much the heat,
it's the humidity that'll kill ya.

550
00:37:00,818 --> 00:37:04,447
[People Chattering
In Foreign Languages]

551
00:37:04,522 --> 00:37:07,047
[P.A. Announcer Speaking
In Foreign Languages]

552
00:37:13,497 --> 00:37:15,988
Excuse me, do you know
where you register for bobsled?

553
00:37:16,067 --> 00:37:19,798
[Chattering, P.A. Continue]

554
00:37:21,872 --> 00:37:24,841
Do you know where
you register for bobsled?

555
00:37:29,113 --> 00:37:31,047
- See ya.
- I'll see ya around.

556
00:37:34,418 --> 00:37:37,819
Hey, Mike. Good to see ya
again, pal. Take care.

557
00:37:37,888 --> 00:37:41,324
- Ja? Okay, ja.
- All the best.

558
00:37:41,392 --> 00:37:44,361
- Can I help you?
- Yeah, I'd like to register for tryouts.

559
00:37:44,428 --> 00:37:47,363
- What country?
- [Clears Throat] Jamaica.

560
00:37:47,431 --> 00:37:50,730
- What country?
- Jamaica.

561
00:37:50,801 --> 00:37:54,066
- [Sighs]
- [Computer Beeps]

562
00:37:54,138 --> 00:37:58,507
Well, what do you know?
Jamaican bobsled team.

563
00:37:58,576 --> 00:38:01,773
Okay. Here it is.
It says here...

564
00:38:01,846 --> 00:38:04,576
your qualifying run will be held
on the evening of the tenth.

565
00:38:04,649 --> 00:38:07,709
Your judges will be Shindler,
Gremmer and Kroychzech.

566
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:11,619
- I know Kroychzech. He's a good guy.
- Yeah. [Clears Throat]

567
00:38:11,689 --> 00:38:14,590
In order to qualify, you must
complete the course safely...

568
00:38:14,659 --> 00:38:17,127
in one-minute,
two-seconds flat or under.

569
00:38:17,194 --> 00:38:19,526
- Used to be a minute-five.
- Yeah.

570
00:38:19,597 --> 00:38:22,293
Times change.

571
00:38:27,705 --> 00:38:30,765
- Irv? Is that you?
- Roger, how ya doin'?

572
00:38:30,841 --> 00:38:34,868
Hello, Kurt.
Been a long time.

573
00:38:34,945 --> 00:38:39,746
Obviously not long enough.
Hello, Larry.

574
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:44,254
Jesus Christ, Irv.
What the hell'd you do to yourself?

575
00:38:46,891 --> 00:38:49,382
- Don't worry about them, Irv.
- Roger, you gotta do me a favor.

576
00:38:49,460 --> 00:38:52,122
- What?
- Please. You know that
revolving restaurant thing?

577
00:38:52,196 --> 00:38:54,494
- Yeah. Half an hour?
- Meet me there in half an hour. Yeah.

578
00:38:54,565 --> 00:38:56,499
- Please!
- [Man] Roger, come on!

579
00:38:56,567 --> 00:38:58,501
[Roger]
I'll try.

580
00:39:14,752 --> 00:39:18,620
- Thanks, Roger.
- Yeah, well. What's up, Irv?

581
00:39:18,689 --> 00:39:22,216
- How about a drink?
- No, I'm fine. What's so
important it couldn't wait?

582
00:39:22,293 --> 00:39:24,420
- You want something to eat?
- No, I m fine. What's up?

583
00:39:24,495 --> 00:39:26,986
- A salad or something...
- Irv!

584
00:39:28,532 --> 00:39:30,124
I need a sled.

585
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:32,761
You came all the way
to Calgary without a sled?

586
00:39:32,837 --> 00:39:36,170
I got $4,800.
I just need something competitive.

587
00:39:36,240 --> 00:39:38,174
[Laughs]
For five grand?

588
00:39:38,242 --> 00:39:40,608
- I know you got something
lying around, Roger.
- But, Irv...

589
00:39:40,678 --> 00:39:44,079
- Anything.
- You know I can't do that.

590
00:39:44,148 --> 00:39:46,878
Wait a minute, Roger.
Remember when you were desperate...

591
00:39:46,951 --> 00:39:49,886
to make that last slot
on the '68 Grenoble team,

592
00:39:49,954 --> 00:39:52,354
and you pleaded with me
to talk to Kurt?

593
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:55,358
Did I say, "Sorry,
Roger, I can't do it"?

594
00:39:55,426 --> 00:40:00,591
Come on, don't make me beg.
Roger, it's me.

595
00:40:00,664 --> 00:40:03,633
All right. Maybe I can get you
one of our practice sleds.

596
00:40:03,701 --> 00:40:07,364
You're a saint. You know that?
You haven't changed a bit.
You're still a saint.

597
00:40:07,438 --> 00:40:10,100
Don't get all mushy on me.
Just tell me one thing.

598
00:40:10,174 --> 00:40:12,142
Is this whole thing a big joke?

599
00:40:12,209 --> 00:40:15,337
Or do you really expect
these Jamaicans to qualify?

600
00:40:15,413 --> 00:40:19,076
Not only are they gonna qualify,
they're gonna turn some heads doin' it.

601
00:40:19,150 --> 00:40:24,417
Listen, three of these guys
can run the hundred in under ten-flat.

602
00:40:24,488 --> 00:40:27,013
I don't care who you are,
that's lightning.

603
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:30,390
Yeah. But can lightning
run on ice?

604
00:40:49,346 --> 00:40:51,439
- No problem, man.
- [Chuckles]

605
00:40:55,386 --> 00:40:58,321
- God!
- [Grunting]

606
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:08,895
Irv! These special shoes
aren't very effective.

607
00:41:19,343 --> 00:41:22,369
Grip with your toes.

608
00:41:22,446 --> 00:41:25,108
All right, you sugarcoated
track stars.

609
00:41:25,182 --> 00:41:28,811
Move out and let the ice-Rasta
show you how it's done.

610
00:41:28,886 --> 00:41:33,687
- Whoa! Ah!
- Yeah, like that. Yeah. Good.

611
00:41:33,757 --> 00:41:36,590
[Junior] Hey, fellas,
look at my progress.

612
00:41:36,660 --> 00:41:39,151
Touchin' me!
[Grunts]

613
00:41:44,335 --> 00:41:46,269
[Buzzer Buzzing]

614
00:41:46,337 --> 00:41:50,239
All right, fellas, that's it.
Let's get off the ice before practice.

615
00:41:50,307 --> 00:41:53,799
- What practice?
- That practice.

616
00:41:53,878 --> 00:41:56,472
[Speaking Russian]

617
00:41:59,183 --> 00:42:03,620
- Whoa. Ah!
- Oh!

618
00:42:06,957 --> 00:42:09,221
[Grunting]

619
00:42:09,293 --> 00:42:12,694
That's right. Ah!

620
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:16,833
Good team this year.

621
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:59,707
Eins, zwei, drei.

622
00:42:59,777 --> 00:43:02,837
[Grunting]

623
00:44:12,850 --> 00:44:16,877
Nice. Bobsleds.

624
00:44:16,954 --> 00:44:21,482
Oh, my. You should see this on the hill.
It's like a miracle.

625
00:44:21,558 --> 00:44:24,322
- What's "schweiz"?
- No, man, Swiss.

626
00:44:24,395 --> 00:44:26,488
[Yul]
This is the real thing, man.

627
00:44:26,563 --> 00:44:31,432
Gentlemen. I'd like to introduce you
to the newest member of our team.

628
00:44:36,640 --> 00:44:39,575
[Irv] Uh, you won't believe
what I had to go through...

629
00:44:39,643 --> 00:44:42,669
to get us a sled
in such good shape.

630
00:44:42,746 --> 00:44:47,649
[Clears Throat] If we're gonna
make it into the Olympics,

631
00:44:47,718 --> 00:44:51,279
this is the boat
that's gonna take us there.

632
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:54,415
Well, I'm told she's
actually quite fast.

633
00:44:54,491 --> 00:44:57,289
[Metal Clattering On Floor]

634
00:44:57,361 --> 00:45:01,991
- L, uh, know she's not much
to look at, but, uh...
- Shh!

635
00:45:02,066 --> 00:45:04,728
She's beautiful.

636
00:45:07,471 --> 00:45:10,702
[Speaking Russian]

637
00:45:16,146 --> 00:45:19,411
[P.A.] All coaches must sign teams in
before approaching bob run.

638
00:45:41,371 --> 00:45:45,273
- [Irv] Here we go.
- [Grunting]

639
00:45:45,342 --> 00:45:47,435
[Irv]
Let's go. Here we go.

640
00:45:49,546 --> 00:45:52,413
- Hold on.
- All right, come on.

641
00:45:52,483 --> 00:45:55,384
[Irv]
Grab ahold. Here we go.

642
00:46:13,370 --> 00:46:17,272
[Sanka]
Ah. This is good.

643
00:46:20,277 --> 00:46:22,609
[Irv]
This is it. Everybody climb in.

644
00:46:22,679 --> 00:46:25,045
Hold up.
I don't understand.

645
00:46:25,115 --> 00:46:28,243
- We're not gonna push start?
- No, we're gonna push start next time.

646
00:46:28,318 --> 00:46:31,082
For your first run,
I'm just gonna nudge you off.

647
00:46:31,155 --> 00:46:34,215
Okay, everybody in. Let's go,
let's go. Come on, come on.

648
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:38,321
- [Yul] Don't touch me.
- Hey, baldy, get off my foot.

649
00:46:38,395 --> 00:46:40,329
- Don't touch me!
- Here we go. Come on.

650
00:46:40,397 --> 00:46:45,164
Hey, Blitzer. Why don't you put
some training wheels on that sled?

651
00:46:45,235 --> 00:46:49,103
- [Crowd Laughing]
- That's funny. Ha-ha. Very funny.

652
00:46:49,173 --> 00:46:53,803
- You want to kiss my egg?
- I'm not kissin' no egg.

653
00:46:53,877 --> 00:46:56,311
- Suit yourself.
- [Irv] Listen up, fellas.

654
00:46:56,380 --> 00:46:59,440
- I don't want you to worry
about lookin' good out there.
- Ah, Blitzy.

655
00:46:59,516 --> 00:47:03,452
You're going to tuck them in too?

656
00:47:03,520 --> 00:47:06,455
Hey. Seemin' to you
like nobody likes us?

657
00:47:06,523 --> 00:47:10,789
We're different. People
always afraid of what's different.

658
00:47:10,861 --> 00:47:13,193
Hey, Jamaica!

659
00:47:13,263 --> 00:47:16,391
Watch out for number 12 turn.
It's scary, ja?

660
00:47:16,466 --> 00:47:17,899
Oooh!

661
00:47:17,968 --> 00:47:20,129
What's his problem?

662
00:47:20,204 --> 00:47:23,332
He's Josef Grool. He's one
of the best drivers in the world.

663
00:47:23,407 --> 00:47:26,274
Yeah, he's one of the biggest
assholes in the world too.

664
00:47:26,343 --> 00:47:30,404
Don't listen to him; you listen to me.
Derice, right here. You got it?

665
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:34,610
Remember, keep your hands soft
and your mind clear.

666
00:47:34,685 --> 00:47:38,678
- High in, low out. What is it?
- High in, low out.

667
00:47:38,755 --> 00:47:41,781
All right, put your helmets on,
everybody. Let's go.

668
00:47:41,859 --> 00:47:43,884
Here we go, come on.
Helmets on.

669
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:48,364
- Hey, coach?
- Yeah.

670
00:47:48,432 --> 00:47:50,627
I cannot get my helmet on.

671
00:47:50,701 --> 00:47:53,499
- Thanks, coach.
- That's what I'm here for.

672
00:47:53,570 --> 00:47:57,165
- Oh, coach? L-I gotta go. You know.
- Yeah?

673
00:47:57,241 --> 00:47:58,833
- Hold it!
- Hold it?

674
00:47:58,909 --> 00:48:01,935
- Hold it! Yeah, hold it!
- Hold it?

675
00:48:02,012 --> 00:48:05,641
B-But, coach, l, I can't hold it.
We're not bobsledding yet.

676
00:48:05,716 --> 00:48:09,812
- Oh, yes, we are.
- Coach! Coach!

677
00:48:14,258 --> 00:48:16,886
Coach! Coach!

678
00:48:20,597 --> 00:48:23,259
[P.A.]
On the track.

679
00:48:26,803 --> 00:48:30,637
[Sanka]
Coach! Aaaaah!

680
00:48:33,443 --> 00:48:36,310
[Sanka]
Aaaaah!

