919
01:04:32,301 --> 01:04:34,963
' Rise above it '

920
01:04:35,037 --> 01:04:40,134
" [Singing In Jamaican]

921
01:04:40,209 --> 01:04:42,905
' Rise above it
You can do it '

922
01:04:42,979 --> 01:04:45,914
' Rise above it
You can do it "

923
01:04:48,517 --> 01:04:50,610
[Irv]
Okay, guys,

924
01:04:50,686 --> 01:04:53,382
tonight's the night.

925
01:04:55,124 --> 01:04:57,524
Now, in a few minutes,
you're gonna get a chance...

926
01:04:57,593 --> 01:05:00,994
to do something that no one
in your country has ever done.

927
01:05:01,063 --> 01:05:04,794
I was gonna save this for the Olympics,
but I figure if we're...

928
01:05:04,867 --> 01:05:09,327
going to convince these judges
that we are world-class sledders,

929
01:05:09,405 --> 01:05:13,364
then we had better look
like world-class sledders.

930
01:05:14,443 --> 01:05:18,539
- Oh, man, yes.
- Oh, man. Nice.

931
01:05:24,353 --> 01:05:26,480
I freeze in this.

932
01:05:26,555 --> 01:05:29,922
[Grunting, Yelling]

933
01:05:32,261 --> 01:05:34,729
[P.A.]
On the track.

934
01:05:41,971 --> 01:05:44,235
Hello, gentlemen.

935
01:05:44,307 --> 01:05:47,799
Irv, this is Karl Shindler.
He'll be watching the middle track.

936
01:05:47,877 --> 01:05:49,777
How do you do?

937
01:05:49,845 --> 01:05:54,282
- And this is August Gremmer.
He'll be judging the push starts.
- Hi.

938
01:05:54,350 --> 01:05:57,615
I'm your third official
up in the tower.

939
01:05:57,687 --> 01:06:00,383
You? What happened
to Kroychzech?

940
01:06:00,456 --> 01:06:03,516
He came down sick this morning.
I'm taking his place.

941
01:06:03,592 --> 01:06:06,493
Oh, goody.

942
01:06:06,562 --> 01:06:09,998
Oh. The Alliance has decided
to change the qualifying time...

943
01:06:10,066 --> 01:06:12,534
from a minute-two
to a minute-flat.

944
01:06:12,601 --> 01:06:15,365
Is that clear?

945
01:06:15,438 --> 01:06:19,465
[Jamaican Accent]
No problem, man.

946
01:06:25,181 --> 01:06:28,048
Go get 'em, kid.

947
01:06:32,855 --> 01:06:35,881
[On Speaker]
Track is clear for Jamaica One.

948
01:06:45,534 --> 01:06:50,699
Eins... zwei... drei.

949
01:06:50,773 --> 01:06:54,402
[Grunting, Yelling]

950
01:06:54,477 --> 01:06:57,139
Go, go, go!
Now, now, now, now!

951
01:07:00,549 --> 01:07:03,780
- All right, what was that time?
- 6.13

952
01:07:44,994 --> 01:07:47,861
Under 60. Is it under 60?

953
01:07:59,475 --> 01:08:02,137
- [Cheering]
- Yes! Derice... Bannock!

954
01:08:02,211 --> 01:08:06,614
Whoo-hoo, 59 points!
[Laughing]

955
01:08:06,682 --> 01:08:11,619
Oh. I'm, uh, I'm sorry.
I'm outta here. That's terrific.

956
01:08:11,687 --> 01:08:14,986
- [Laughing Continues]
- [Cheering Continues]

957
01:08:15,057 --> 01:08:17,821
Derice!

958
01:08:17,893 --> 01:08:20,987
- " [Reggae]
- [Irv] Ah, it was great.

959
01:08:21,063 --> 01:08:24,260
[Derice] They couldn't beat us.
I know we were the best.

960
01:08:24,333 --> 01:08:27,632
[Irv]
...inspired you guys, that's all.

961
01:08:27,703 --> 01:08:32,163
Nobody had that much fun
in a sled since Santa Claus.

962
01:08:32,241 --> 01:08:35,039
Fellas, here's
to followin' your dreams.

963
01:08:35,111 --> 01:08:37,079
- Yeah, man.
- [Together] Followin' your dreams.

964
01:08:37,146 --> 01:08:40,479
I said it to your father the first time
I met him, and I'll say it again.

965
01:08:40,549 --> 01:08:44,610
- Sprinters make the best bobsledders.
- Here's to sprinting.

966
01:08:44,687 --> 01:08:47,747
So, what are we gonna
name the sled?

967
01:08:47,823 --> 01:08:50,792
How about "Tallulah"?

968
01:08:50,860 --> 01:08:53,260
- [Laughter]
- Tallulah.

969
01:08:53,329 --> 01:08:55,820
Tallulah.

970
01:08:55,898 --> 01:08:59,698
Sounds like a two-dollar hooker.
How you come up with that?

971
01:08:59,768 --> 01:09:04,398
Hey, you idiot,
that's my mother's name.

972
01:09:04,473 --> 01:09:06,498
- It's a pretty name.
- Tallulah. I like that.

973
01:09:06,575 --> 01:09:08,873
So, what's it gonna be, star?

974
01:09:08,944 --> 01:09:11,845
What are the people gonna be screamin'
when Jamaica takes the hill?

975
01:09:11,914 --> 01:09:16,146
I say we call it
"Cool runnings."

976
01:09:16,218 --> 01:09:18,186
- [Yul] Beautiful.
- I like it.

977
01:09:18,254 --> 01:09:20,552
- It's very strong.
- Nice. Very nice.

978
01:09:20,623 --> 01:09:23,490
Uh, what exactly does it mean?

979
01:09:23,559 --> 01:09:26,960
"Cool runnings" means
"Peace be the journey."

980
01:09:27,029 --> 01:09:28,963
[Together]
Peace be the journey.

981
01:09:29,031 --> 01:09:32,364
- Cool runnings.
- [Together] Cool runnings.

982
01:09:32,434 --> 01:09:36,097
- [Clears Throat] Excuse me.
- To the man in the orange suit!

983
01:09:36,172 --> 01:09:39,539
[Laughing, Shouting]

984
01:09:39,608 --> 01:09:43,066
- To the messenger!
- [Together] To the messenger.

985
01:09:43,145 --> 01:09:45,807
[Laughing, Shouting Continue]

986
01:09:45,881 --> 01:09:48,816
[Sighing]

987
01:09:48,884 --> 01:09:53,446
We are officially...
disqualified.

988
01:10:01,363 --> 01:10:05,231
- [Chattering, Laughing]
- Excuse me, gentlemen.

989
01:10:05,301 --> 01:10:07,428
Kurt, I really
have to talk to you.

990
01:10:07,503 --> 01:10:10,495
Excuse me, Irv.
I've nothing to say to you.

991
01:10:10,573 --> 01:10:14,737
Yes, you do. I want to know
why you disqualified my guys.

992
01:10:14,810 --> 01:10:18,906
As you were told, your team must
compete in an international race
to qualify for the Olympics.

993
01:10:18,981 --> 01:10:23,384
But in an Olympic year, the qualifiers
count as an international race.

994
01:10:23,452 --> 01:10:26,285
That may have been true
in past Olympic years,

995
01:10:26,355 --> 01:10:29,813
but this year the Alliance
decided to change its policy.

996
01:10:29,892 --> 01:10:32,861
Oh, please.
Change its policy?

997
01:10:32,928 --> 01:10:37,058
The Alliance has the right to do
whatever they feel is in the best
interest of the sport.

998
01:10:37,132 --> 01:10:41,466
We must also be concerned about
the potential for embarrassment.

999
01:10:41,537 --> 01:10:43,471
Oh, forgive me.

1000
01:10:43,539 --> 01:10:47,407
I didn't realize that four black guys
in a bobsled could make you blush.

1001
01:10:47,476 --> 01:10:50,104
[Shindler]
I think we've heard enough.

1002
01:10:50,179 --> 01:10:53,410
Come on, Kurt. What you're doin'
is wrong and you know it.

1003
01:10:53,482 --> 01:10:57,612
Now, if this is about you and me,
then let's get it straight right now.

1004
01:10:57,686 --> 01:11:02,623
All right, 16 years ago,
I made the biggest mistake of my life.

1005
01:11:02,691 --> 01:11:06,457
I cheated. I was stupid.

1006
01:11:06,528 --> 01:11:09,895
I embarrassed myself,
my family,

1007
01:11:09,965 --> 01:11:13,628
my teammates, my country
and my coach.

1008
01:11:15,738 --> 01:11:18,764
If it's revenge you want,
take it.

1009
01:11:18,841 --> 01:11:21,833
Go ahead.
Disqualify me, banish me.

1010
01:11:21,910 --> 01:11:24,003
Do whatever you want,
but do it to me.

1011
01:11:24,079 --> 01:11:27,879
It was me who let you down, Kurt.
It wasn't my guys.

1012
01:11:27,950 --> 01:11:30,282
They've done everything
you've asked of them.

1013
01:11:30,352 --> 01:11:33,844
And they did it with all of you
laughing in their face.

1014
01:11:33,922 --> 01:11:38,382
Hell, it doesn't matter
if they come in first or 50th.

1015
01:11:38,460 --> 01:11:41,827
Those guys have earned the right
to represent their country.

1016
01:11:41,897 --> 01:11:45,492
They've earned the right
to march into that stadium...

1017
01:11:45,567 --> 01:11:47,501
and wave their nation's flag.

1018
01:11:47,569 --> 01:11:52,097
That's the single greatest honor
an athlete could ever have.

1019
01:11:54,043 --> 01:11:57,410
That's what the Olympics
are about.

1020
01:11:58,681 --> 01:12:02,344
Sixteen years ago,
I forgot that.

1021
01:12:02,418 --> 01:12:05,478
Don't you go and do the same.

1022
01:12:08,057 --> 01:12:11,117
[Sighing] I'm sorry
if I interrupted your meeting.

1023
01:12:19,735 --> 01:12:22,397
[Ringing]

1024
01:12:23,472 --> 01:12:27,169
Hello? Yes.

1025
01:12:29,645 --> 01:12:32,375
Yeah.

1026
01:12:33,782 --> 01:12:36,751
Right. Good-bye.

1027
01:12:39,555 --> 01:12:44,424
- What?
- Oh, it's the Alliance. God.

1028
01:12:44,493 --> 01:12:47,257
What did they say?

1029
01:12:47,329 --> 01:12:49,593
Aw, they said we're back in.

1030
01:12:49,665 --> 01:12:52,964
[Cheering]

1031
01:12:53,035 --> 01:12:55,196
Yes! Yes, yes!

1032
01:12:55,270 --> 01:12:57,898
[Cheering Continues]

1033
01:13:06,382 --> 01:13:09,146
[Man On Television] And a lot
is expected of the Italian team.

1034
01:13:09,218 --> 01:13:11,482
Did I miss it? Did I miss it?

1035
01:13:11,553 --> 01:13:14,579
No, child,
you didn't miss a thing.

1036
01:13:14,656 --> 01:13:17,284
[Broadcast Continues]... of Jamaica
made it all the way here to Calgary...

1037
01:13:17,359 --> 01:13:20,294
to compete in the bobsled event.

1038
01:13:20,362 --> 01:13:22,830
Their flag bearer is
the sled captain Derice Bannock.

1039
01:13:22,898 --> 01:13:25,833
Derice's father, Ben Bannock,
was a gold medalist in the 200 meters...

1040
01:13:25,901 --> 01:13:29,234
at the Summer Olympic Games
over 20 years ago.

1041
01:13:29,304 --> 01:13:32,535
And perhaps there's gold
in two generations of this family.

1042
01:13:32,608 --> 01:13:35,577
That's quite a story.
The Jamaican bobsled team.

1043
01:13:35,644 --> 01:13:39,239
It's a beautiful afternoon in Calgary,
and there is a lot more coming up.

1044
01:13:39,314 --> 01:13:43,375
So stay tuned for more exciting coverage
of the opening ceremonies...

1045
01:13:43,452 --> 01:13:47,445
of the 15th Winter Olympiad
from Calgary, Alberta, Canada.

1046
01:13:54,530 --> 01:13:58,864
Gentlemen, let's go check
into our new home. Come on, Junior.

1047
01:14:06,308 --> 01:14:08,742
[Irv]
Junior! Hey!

1048
01:14:13,248 --> 01:14:15,182
Junior!

1049
01:14:18,487 --> 01:14:20,546
Now, a lot of coaches
would be giving you...

1050
01:14:20,622 --> 01:14:23,591
one of those "Win one for the Gipper"
speeches.

1051
01:14:23,659 --> 01:14:26,856
I'm not good at that stuff.
Instead, I thought I'd, uh,

1052
01:14:26,929 --> 01:14:29,557
lead you in a psalm
of inspiration.

1053
01:14:29,631 --> 01:14:31,724
Let's bow our heads.

1054
01:14:31,800 --> 01:14:33,734
- Who's the "Gipper"?
- Shh.

1055
01:14:33,802 --> 01:14:38,739
Our Father who art in Calgary,
bobsled be Thy name.

1056
01:14:38,807 --> 01:14:41,640
Thy kingdom come,
gold medals won...

1057
01:14:41,710 --> 01:14:44,702
- [Giggling]
- On Earth as it is in turn seven.

1058
01:14:44,780 --> 01:14:47,271
With liberty and justice
for Jamaica and Haile Selassie.

1059
01:14:47,349 --> 01:14:49,817
- Amen.
- All right.

1060
01:14:49,885 --> 01:14:52,080
- Respect.
- [Knock At Door]

1061
01:14:52,154 --> 01:14:54,622
- All right.
- Jah Rastafari.

1062
01:14:54,690 --> 01:14:57,124
[Chattering]

1063
01:14:59,761 --> 01:15:02,696
[Chattering Continues]

1064
01:15:03,932 --> 01:15:05,866
Junior?

1065
01:15:11,206 --> 01:15:15,370
Now, you listen to me, boy.

1066
01:15:15,444 --> 01:15:17,844
You might not have done
what you were asked,

1067
01:15:17,913 --> 01:15:20,780
but you will do
what you're told.

1068
01:15:20,849 --> 01:15:23,909
- You're coming home.
- But, Father, you know I just want...

1069
01:15:23,986 --> 01:15:25,920
But nothing.

1070
01:15:25,988 --> 01:15:28,286
I didn't send you
to the finest school...

1071
01:15:28,357 --> 01:15:31,224
for you to go around
sliding on your backside.

1072
01:15:31,293 --> 01:15:35,229
- You must be mad.
- Yeah, but the team needs me.

1073
01:15:35,297 --> 01:15:38,892
- I don't want to hear any more about it.
- [Elevator Bell Rings]

1074
01:15:38,967 --> 01:15:41,902
Go and get your things.

1075
01:15:52,814 --> 01:15:55,180
I'll wait in the lobby.

1076
01:15:58,987 --> 01:16:03,083
- [Elevator Bell Rings]
- Pride. Power.

1077
01:16:06,628 --> 01:16:11,065
Father, when you look at me,
what do you see?

1078
01:16:11,133 --> 01:16:16,765
- I don't have time for games, Junior.
- Tell me what you see, please!

1079
01:16:16,838 --> 01:16:19,602
All right,
I'll tell you what I see.

1080
01:16:19,675 --> 01:16:21,609
I see a lost little boy...

1081
01:16:21,677 --> 01:16:24,612
who's lucky to have a father
who knows what's best for him.

1082
01:16:24,680 --> 01:16:26,113
[Elevator Bell Rings]

1083
01:16:26,181 --> 01:16:29,116
No, no, no, no, you don't know
what's best for me, Father.

1084
01:16:29,184 --> 01:16:33,018
I am not a lost little boy,
Father.

1085
01:16:33,088 --> 01:16:37,525
I am a man.
And I'm an Olympian.

1086
01:16:40,062 --> 01:16:42,792
I'm stayin' right here.

1087
01:16:45,233 --> 01:16:47,667
[Elevator Bell Rings]

1088
01:16:53,909 --> 01:16:56,139
Hey, Junior Bevil.

1089
01:16:56,211 --> 01:16:59,146
You're a badass mother.

1090
01:17:09,691 --> 01:17:12,854
[Chattering]

1091
01:17:15,364 --> 01:17:19,095
- Here, I got a couple.
- I like this one, yes.

1092
01:17:21,036 --> 01:17:24,597
[Foreign Languages]

1093
01:17:24,673 --> 01:17:28,074
Oh, Canada, indeed. This is Al Trautwig
along with John Morgan.

1094
01:17:28,143 --> 01:17:30,703
We're live at Olympic Park,
the brand-new bobsledding venue...

1095
01:17:30,779 --> 01:17:33,179
just a few miles outside
of downtown Calgary.

1096
01:17:33,248 --> 01:17:36,183
- Everybody, shut up. It's starting.
...extremely intense,

1097
01:17:36,251 --> 01:17:38,947
exciting competition
for the next three days.

1098
01:17:42,224 --> 01:17:44,818
[Chattering]

1099
01:17:47,596 --> 01:17:51,430
I am feeling very Olympic today.
How about you?

1100
01:17:54,202 --> 01:17:56,636
[Al Trautwig On TV] This sport, as we
well know, is made up of athletes...

1101
01:17:56,705 --> 01:17:59,469
who go to the edge and sometimes beyond,
and it is why we believe...

1102
01:17:59,541 --> 01:18:03,033
the next three days is going to be
extremely competitive and exciting.

1103
01:18:03,111 --> 01:18:06,911
And already, John, on day one,
we're starting things off
with a gold medal favorite.

1104
01:18:06,982 --> 01:18:09,746
Well, the Swiss were fortunate enough
to draw number one in the competition.

1105
01:18:09,818 --> 01:18:12,116
We gotta make them the odds-on favorite
to win the gold.

1106
01:18:12,187 --> 01:18:15,384
But the East Germans, they're coming off
the gold medal win in 1984.

1107
01:18:15,457 --> 01:18:17,982
The Canadians, it's their home track.
You gotta favor them too.

1108
01:18:18,060 --> 01:18:21,257
And they've been doin'
very well in practice all week.

1109
01:18:22,431 --> 01:18:26,162
[Shouting In German]

1110
01:18:27,602 --> 01:18:30,469
- Eins, zwei, drei.
- Eins, zwei, drei.

1111
01:18:30,539 --> 01:18:33,440
- [Grunting]
- [Cheering]

1112
01:18:36,445 --> 01:18:40,074
One, two, three, go!

1113
01:18:48,523 --> 01:18:51,754
[Cheering Continues]

1114
01:18:51,827 --> 01:18:55,228
[Al Trautwig On TV]
Eighty miles an hour or close to it.

1115
01:18:55,297 --> 01:18:59,563
You know, Al, I'm looking at
the times here, and the course
is gettin' extremely fast.

1116
01:18:59,634 --> 01:19:03,593
I was worried about
the Austrian team's safety in that
last big 180 degree whiparound.

1117
01:19:03,672 --> 01:19:07,108
Well, if you were worried
about them, what are you thinking
about our last and next team?

1118
01:19:07,175 --> 01:19:10,542
Yes, it certainly
seems strange that surrounded
by the ice and snow of Calgary,

1119
01:19:10,612 --> 01:19:14,605
we are about to watch a team
from the tiny island of Jamaica.

1120
01:19:14,683 --> 01:19:18,278
- [Cheering]
- Yeah, from Jamaica!

1121
01:19:18,353 --> 01:19:20,913
Quite a story for them to even get here.
They came out of nowhere.

1122
01:19:20,989 --> 01:19:23,048
And you know, there's a lot of teams
up here on top of the hill...

1123
01:19:23,125 --> 01:19:25,889
that sort of feel that Jamaicans
don't belong here.

1124
01:19:25,961 --> 01:19:28,759
[Booing]

1125
01:19:33,201 --> 01:19:36,693
- Hey! Hey! What are you doin'?
- Hey, what are you doin', man?

1126
01:19:36,772 --> 01:19:39,002
That's what the Swiss do
to psyche themselves up.

1127
01:19:39,074 --> 01:19:42,635
They also make them little pocketknives,
too, but I don't see you doin' that.

1128
01:19:42,711 --> 01:19:46,340
All right, guys, we're up. Come on. Hey,
knock it off. Knock it off, will ya?

1129
01:19:46,414 --> 01:19:49,611
Okay, let's go. Come on.
Get in your start positions.

1130
01:19:49,684 --> 01:19:53,814
We don't have to win the gold in the
first day. It's just like any other run.

1131
01:19:53,889 --> 01:19:56,858
Except this time,
100 million people watchin'.

